<p>This library implements the base58 encoding algorithm. It&apos;s basically base64 but
with a smaller alphabet (58, as in the title) that doesn&apos;t include similar
looking characters,
<a href="https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/base58.h" >among other things</a>.</p>

<p>The implementation is essentially a carbon copy of Gavin Andresen&apos;s
<a href="https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=1026.0" >Python code</a>.</p>

<h1>Usage</h1>

<pre><code><span class="code">cl-user&gt; <span class="paren1">(<span class="code">base58:encode <span class="string">"this is a test"</span></span>)</span>
"jo91waLQA1NNeBmZKUF"
cl-user&gt; <span class="paren1">(<span class="code">base58:decode <span class="string">"jo91waLQA1NNeBmZKUF"</span></span>)</span>
"this is a test"</span></code></pre>

<h1>Tests</h1>

<p>The encoded strings in the tests were created with Andresen&apos;s unmodified code,
so they are correct. Probably.</p>

